description: Two handshakes, a Pageau chant and the Minnesota Wild live to die another day. On todays #LOSP, Ross Levitan and Brandon Piller touch on Connor Brown's breakout game at the World Championships and why Sens fans shouldn't be concerned with Abramov choosing to continue his development overseas before breaking down a very entertaining series finale between the Penguins and Islanders. Then, we invite on this weeks SensCentral Citizen Kurt Watkins (@KurtCMWatkins) for some off-season hot takes and his origin story! Finally, we preview tonights slate of NHL action, give our respect to Ethan Bear and spin the Tankathon wheel.
